  "doc_id": "48163",
  "text": "Rotating machines, such as centrifugal compressors, are widely used due to their high performance and robustness [CITATION_1] . These machines typically operate under adverse conditions such as high pressures and speeds. Therefore, performance deterioration and failure are unavoidable. In order to solve this problem, data-driven machine health monitoring systems (MHMS) [CITATION_2] were introduced to realize predictive maintenance. Data-driven MHMS comprises four main steps: extracting features from collected data, detecting an incipient fault, determining the variables mostly associated with the fault and implementing a prognostic model to predict machine degradation. It is clear that these technical processes are crucial for the safe, efficient and sustainable operation of any rotating machinery. Therefore, it is not surprising that automated data-driven machine health monitoring has become increasingly popular in recent years.",
